result.execSummary:
The defendant Trevor I. Unseth was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Trevor I. Unseth is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Trevor I. Unseth was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
From VARC on copies of criminal complaint. Invoice  was sent out via email.

09/05-Payment received and copies were sent out via mail.

Attorney Michael Yang in court with Defendant Trevor I. Unseth in person from jail. Prosecuting Atty Amy Elizabeth Forehand appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Plea agreement stated for cases 16CM76 and 16CM3.

Def pleads no contest to disorderly conduct/count 1 in 16CM76 and to disorderly conduct/count 1 and criminal damage to property/count 2 in 16CM3.  Court's colloquy on pleas.  Finding of guilty.

Sentence:

16CM76 - 30 days jail with 31 days credit - time served sentence.  Costs remitted in this case.

16CM3 - Sentence withheld for 18 months probation.  Conditions:  attend, pay for, and succ. complete any treatment/programming; AODA/follow through; restitution and costs, both as conditions of probation; attend/succ. complete d.a. education class.  Restitution amount:  $1266 to LM.
Status conference on July 14, 2016 at 11:00 am.

Defendant Trevor I. Unseth in court with attorney Michael Yang. Prosecuting Atty Amy Forehand appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Adjourned initial in 16CM76 and plea/sentencing in 16CM3.

16CM76 - formal reading waived.  Court states charges and informs def of the possible max. penalties.  NG pleas entered on def's behalf.  Status requested and set for 7/14 at 11.  That will be date for plea/sentencing in 16CM3.  Status conference scheduled for July 14, 2016 at 11:00 am.
Adjourned initial appearance on June 22, 2016 at 10:00 am.
Request for rescheduling made by SPD.
def via video from Richland County jail
Adjourned initial appearance on June 20, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

1:23 p.m. Defendant Trevor I. Unseth via video from Richland County Jail. Prosecuting Atty Amy Elizabeth Forehand appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Court informs def of the charges/max possible penalties as well as right to counsel. Court will adjourn until next week, def is instructed to contact SPD. Court also requests scheduling in 16CM3 as well. Court states if that date does not work for Attorney Yang, he may request rescheduling.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for June 20, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
